data.title: About
data.text:
LACoSLSA represents the Los Angeles County lifeguards and junior lifeguards in regional, national and international lifesaving sports events. It is supported by volunteer efforts and is a key component of developing personnel safety skills and knowledge. Members must be Los Angeles County lifeguards, junior lifeguards or alumni â€“ additional information on how to become a team member is located below. The team competes in a variety of events throughout the year, many of which are open to the public and to which LACoSLSA provides support. Our EIN is 46-5086290.

The goal of the surf racing team is to generate an enthusiastic group of competitors, all of whom have an equal opportunity to benefit from increased sponsorship, revenue and competition opportunities. Lifeguards and junior guards who give their time and effort to assist the team and help raise funds shall benefit most for their effort. All lifeguards, junior guards and alumni who fulfill the requirements will make the LA County Surf Racing Team.

All team members must at least 4 hours at one of our volunteer events and compete in one or more of the surf lifesaving competitions.
